{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 SmartTransit Backend Version Policy Handbook\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Last updated: 2026-03-05 Audience: New and existing backend developers\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 Purpose\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This handbook defines the approved versions for backend development and explains {\b why each version choice matters}. The goal is simple:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab predictable builds,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab fewer environment-related bugs,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab safer dependency upgrades,\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab faster onboarding for new team members.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If your local setup differs from this handbook, align to this document first.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
