{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 4) Known Out-of-Scope Versions (Backend Repo)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The following are {\b not pinned in this backend repository} and must be controlled in the frontend/mobile repository:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Flutter SDK version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Android Gradle Plugin version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Gradle wrapper version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 compileSdkVersion}, {\f1 targetSdkVersion}, {\f1 minSdkVersion}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Android Build Tools version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Kotlin version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Android build JDK version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab iOS deployment target / Xcode version\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Why this is out-of-scope: these versions belong to app build pipelines, not backend build/runtime.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 5) Rules for New and Existing Developers\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Use {\b Go 1.24.5} locally.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Do not manually edit dependency versions outside normal {\f1 go mod} workflow.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Run checks before pushing: {\f1 make check}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Keep Docker and Go versions aligned (Go toolchain in {\f1 go.mod} and {\f1 Dockerfile} must match).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Update this handbook in the same PR whenever version policy changes.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 6) Safe Upgrade Process\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When upgrading any core version:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Create a small PR focused only on the version bump.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Run {\f1 go mod tidy}, tests, and basic endpoint smoke tests.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Check authentication, database, and payment-related flows.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Update this handbook and {\f1 TECH_STACK_AND_DEPENDENCIES.md} together.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Merge only after at least one teammate validates locally.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 7) Quick Onboarding Checklist\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Install Go {\b 1.24.5}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Pull latest code.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Run {\f1 make install-deps}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Configure {\f1 .env} from {\f1 .env.example}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Start backend: {\f1 make run}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Verify health endpoint: {\f1 http://localhost:8080/health}.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If your environment does not match expected behavior, first re-check your versions against this handbook.\par}
